{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-11",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_11_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 11 - Gutman",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 6,
  "page_start_sec": 0.66,
  "page_end_sec": 241.1,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.658,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.66,
      "end": 9.78,
      "text": "XI."
    },
    {
      "start": 9.96,
      "end": 10.96,
      "text": "GUTMAN"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.79,
      "end": 16.22,
      "text": "The telephone bell was ringing when Spade returned to his office,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 16.4,
      "end": 17.7,
      "text": "after sending Bridget"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.78,
      "end": 19.7,
      "text": "O'Shaughnessy off to Effie Pryne's house."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.62,
      "end": 21.52,
      "text": "He went to the telephone.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 22.66,
      "end": 22.94,
      "text": "\"'Hello?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 23.12,
      "end": 23.96,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.02,
      "end": 24.74,
      "text": "this is Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.94,
      "end": 25.04,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 25.78,
      "end": 26.3,
      "text": "I got it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 27.16,
      "end": 28.32,
      "text": "I've been waiting to hear from you.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 28.46,
      "end": 28.56,
      "text": "Who?"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.28,
      "end": 29.44,
      "text": "Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 30.08,
      "end": 30.32,
      "text": "Gutman?"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.54,
      "end": 31.18,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.22,
      "end": 31.42,
      "text": "yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 31.46,
      "end": 31.76,
      "text": "sure."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.01,
      "end": 32.66,
      "text": "Now."
    },
    {
      "start": 32.96,
      "end": 34.12,
      "text": "The sooner the better."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.008,
      "end": 35.4,
      "text": "Twelve C.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 35.68,
      "end": 36.12,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.36,
      "end": 37.94,
      "text": "Say fifteen minutes."
    },
    {
      "start": 38.92,
      "end": 39.18,
      "text": "Right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 40.704,
      "end": 42.64,
      "text": "Spade sat on the corner of the desk beside",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 42.64,
      "end": 44.22,
      "text": "the telephone and rolled a cigarette."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.84,
      "end": 46.42,
      "text": "His mouth was a hard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.54,
      "end": 47.22,
      "text": "complacent V."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.48,
      "end": 48.64,
      "text": "His eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 48.86,
      "end": 50.46,
      "text": "watching his fingers make the cigarette,"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.944,
      "end": 53.12,
      "text": "smoldered over lower lids drawn up tight."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.87,
      "end": 56.42,
      "text": "The door opened and Iva Archer came in.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 56.58,
      "end": 58.04,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.56,
      "end": 58.96,
      "text": "\"'Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 59.06,
      "end": 61.26,
      "text": "honey,' in a voice as lightly amiable"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.26,
      "end": 63.16,
      "text": "as his face had suddenly become."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.98,
      "end": 64.6,
      "text": "\"'Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 64.62,
      "end": 64.9,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 65.2,
      "end": 66.02,
      "text": "forgive me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.18,
      "end": 69.2,
      "text": "forgive me,' she cried in a choked voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.7,
      "end": 72.28,
      "text": "She stood just inside the door,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 72.48,
      "end": 74.94,
      "text": "wadding a black-bordered handkerchief in her small"
    },
    {
      "start": 74.98,
      "end": 75.6,
      "text": "gloved hands,"
    },
    {
      "start": 75.96,
      "end": 79.3,
      "text": "peering into his face with frightened red and swollen eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.27,
      "end": 82.78,
      "text": "He did not get up from his seat on the desk corner.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 83.42,
      "end": 83.7,
      "text": "He said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.02,
      "end": 84.68,
      "text": "Sure,"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.94,
      "end": 85.64,
      "text": "that's all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 85.8,
      "end": 86.976,
      "text": "Forget it.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 87.9,
      "end": 90.26,
      "text": "She came to him and put her hands on his shoulders.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 91.0,
      "end": 91.5,
      "text": "\"'But,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 91.5,
      "end": 93.14,
      "text": "Sam!' she wailed."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.24,
      "end": 95.34,
      "text": "\"'I sent those policemen there."
    },
    {
      "start": 96.4,
      "end": 97.02,
      "text": "I was mad,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 97.38,
      "end": 98.4,
      "text": "crazy with jealousy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 99.04,
      "end": 101.22,
      "text": "and I phoned them that if they'd go there they'd"
    },
    {
      "start": 101.22,
      "end": 103.26,
      "text": "learn something about Miles's murder.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.48,
      "end": 105.68,
      "text": "\"'What made you think that?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 106.22,
      "end": 106.64,
      "text": "\"'Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 106.64,
      "end": 107.16,
      "text": "I didn't,"
    },
    {
      "start": 107.16,
      "end": 107.46,
      "text": "Sam."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.12,
      "end": 108.88,
      "text": "But I was mad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.06,
      "end": 110.656,
      "text": "and I wanted to hurt you.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.94,
      "end": 113.08,
      "text": "made things damn awkward.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 113.62,
      "end": 116.16,
      "text": "He put his arm around her and drew her nearer."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.12,
      "end": 118.1,
      "text": "But it's all right now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 118.38,
      "end": 121.16,
      "text": "only don't get any more crazy ideas like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 122.16,
      "end": 122.8,
      "text": "I won't,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 122.8,
      "end": 123.62,
      "text": "she promised."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.82,
      "end": 124.6,
      "text": "I won't."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.44,
      "end": 127.28,
      "text": "But you weren't nice to me last night.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 128.032,
      "end": 131.2,
      "text": "You were cold and distant and wanted to get rid of me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 131.34,
      "end": 133.98,
      "text": "When I'd come down there and waited and"
    },
    {
      "start": 134.08,
      "end": 135.02,
      "text": "waited to warn you,"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.1,
      "end": 137.2,
      "text": "and you—warn me about what?"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.14,
      "end": 138.64,
      "text": "About Phil.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 138.9,
      "end": 140.704,
      "text": "He's found out about—about"
    },
    {
      "start": 141.68,
      "end": 142.7,
      "text": "you being in love with me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 142.82,
      "end": 145.38,
      "text": "and Miles had told him about my wanting a divorce,"
    },
    {
      "start": 145.62,
      "end": 146.36,
      "text": "though of"
    },
    {
      "start": 146.36,
      "end": 148.02,
      "text": "course he never knew what for,"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.24,
      "end": 150.36,
      "text": "and now Phil thinks we..."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.36,
      "end": 152.1,
      "text": "you killed his brother because"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.54,
      "end": 154.88,
      "text": "he wouldn't give me the divorce so we could get married."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.45,
      "end": 157.48,
      "text": "He told me he believed that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.9,
      "end": 160.44,
      "text": "and yesterday he went and told the police.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 161.76,
      "end": 164.0,
      "text": "\"'That's nice,' Spade said softly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 164.98,
      "end": 166.18,
      "text": "\"'And you came to warn me,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 166.7,
      "end": 167.78,
      "text": "and because I was busy"
    },
    {
      "start": 168.14,
      "end": 169.52,
      "text": "You got up on your ear and helped"
    },
    {
      "start": 169.52,
      "end": 171.48,
      "text": "this damn Phil Archer mess things up."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.64,
      "end": 173.18,
      "text": "I'm sorry,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 174.0,
      "end": 174.54,
      "text": "she whimpered.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 175.24,
      "end": 176.66,
      "text": "I know you won't forgive me.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 177.344,
      "end": 178.52,
      "text": "I'm sorry,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 178.82,
      "end": 179.36,
      "text": "sorry,"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.54,
      "end": 179.9,
      "text": "sorry."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.34,
      "end": 182.0,
      "text": "You ought to be,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 182.62,
      "end": 183.0,
      "text": "he agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.64,
      "end": 185.34,
      "text": "on your own account as well as mine."
    },
    {
      "start": 186.42,
      "end": 188.76,
      "text": "Has Dundee been to see you since Phil did his talking?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 189.36,
      "end": 190.52,
      "text": "Or anybody from the hall?"
    },
    {
      "start": 191.16,
      "end": 191.78,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.928,
      "end": 194.46,
      "text": "Alarm opened her eyes and mouth.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 195.64,
      "end": 195.94,
      "text": "They will,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 196.16,
      "end": 196.74,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.86,
      "end": 200.56,
      "text": "And it'd be just as well not to let them find you here.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 201.14,
      "end": 203.3,
      "text": "Did you tell them who you were when you phoned?"
    },
    {
      "start": 204.14,
      "end": 204.44,
      "text": "Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 204.46,
      "end": 204.64,
      "text": "no."
    },
    {
      "start": 205.04,
      "end": 207.72,
      "text": "I just told them that if they'd go to your apartment then,"
    },
    {
      "start": 208.0,
      "end": 210.1,
      "text": "they'd learn something about the murder and hung up."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.488,
      "end": 212.16,
      "text": "Where'd you phone from?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 213.26,
      "end": 214.84,
      "text": "The drugstore up above your place.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 215.64,
      "end": 215.94,
      "text": "Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 215.96,
      "end": 216.32,
      "text": "Sam,"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.44,
      "end": 216.78,
      "text": "dearest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 216.94,
      "end": 217.6,
      "text": "I—"
    },
    {
      "start": 217.76,
      "end": 220.3,
      "text": "He patted her shoulder and said pleasantly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 221.48,
      "end": 222.42,
      "text": "It was a dumb trick,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 222.5,
      "end": 222.88,
      "text": "all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 222.96,
      "end": 223.98,
      "text": "but it's done now."
    },
    {
      "start": 225.056,
      "end": 226.64,
      "text": "You'd better run along home and think",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 226.64,
      "end": 228.04,
      "text": "up some things to tell the police."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.14,
      "end": 230.12,
      "text": "You'll be hearing from them.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 231.072,
      "end": 234.784,
      "text": "Maybe it'd be best to say no right across the board.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 235.1,
      "end": 237.34,
      "text": "He frowned at something in the distance."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.46,
      "end": 241.1,
      "text": "\"'Or maybe you'd better see Sid Wise first.'",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}